{
  "id": "5760336e2957b90134ede223",
  "name": "Intrusion into the Democratic National Committee",
  "description": "CrowdStrike Services Inc., our Incident Response group, was called by the Democratic National Committee (DNC), the formal governing body for the US Democratic Party, to respond to a suspected breach. We deployed our IR team andtechnologyand immediately identified two sophisticated adversaries on the network \u2013 COZY BEAR and FANCY BEAR. In fact, our team considers them some of the best adversaries out of all the numerous nation-state, criminal and hacktivist/terrorist groups we encounter on a daily basis. In particular, we identified advanced methods consistent with nation-state level capabilities including deliberate targeting and \u2018access management\u2019 tradecraft \u2013 both groups were constantly going back into the environment to change out their implants, modify persistent methods, move to new Command &amp; Control channels and perform other tasks to try to stay ahead of being detected.",
  "author_name": "AlienVault",
